text: Anne-Marie Pålsson (born 23 April 1951) is a Swedish politician and economist. She was a member of the Swedish parliament for the Moderate Party between 2002 and 2010. She is also known for starting the Housemaid debate in July 1993. == References == ==Other websites== *Anne-Marie Pålsson at the Parliament of Sweden website Category:1951 births Category:Living people Category:Swedish economists Category:Swedish politicians
